quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  61,1,"Whatever there is in the heavens and the earth glorifies Allah, and He is the All-mighty, the All-wise"
  61,2,O you who have faith! Why do you say what you do not do
  61,3,It is greatly outrageous to Allah that you should say what you do not do
  61,4,"Indeed Allah loves those who fight in His way in ranks, as if they were a compact structure"
  61,5,"When Moses said to his people, ‘O my people! Why do you torment me, when you certainly know that I am Allah’s apostle to you?’ So when they swerved [from the right path], Allah made their hearts swerve, and Allah does not guide the transgressing lot"
  61,6,"And when Jesus son of Mary said, ‘O Children of Israel! Indeed I am the apostle of Allah to you, to confirm what is before me of the Torah, and to give the good news of an apostle who will come after me, whose name is Ahmad.’ But when he brought them manifest proofs, they said, ‘This is plain magic.’"
  61,7,"Who is a greater wrongdoer than him who fabricates falsehoods against Allah, while he is being summoned to Islam? And Allah does not guide the wrongdoing lot"
  61,8,"They desire to put out the light of Allah with their mouths, but Allah will perfect His light though the faithless should be averse"
  61,9,It is He who has sent His Apostle with guidance and the true religion that He may make it prevail over all religions though the polytheists should be averse